Evaluation: Success is measured by an increase in the number of qualified leads generated, a more consistent pipeline, and a reduction in desperation or reliance on low-probability deals.

Additional Resources:

"Fanatical Prospecting" by Jeb Blount (book)
Articles and resources on effective prospecting techniques
Chapter 7: Dual Process – Balancing Relationships and Outcomes
Key Concept: Sales success requires a balance between building strong relationships and focusing on achieving sales objectives.

Practical Application 1: Shifting from "People-Pleaser" to "Trusted Advisor"

Actionable Task 7.1: Define Your Boundaries:
Steps: Set clear expectations for yourself and your prospects regarding your time, availability, and willingness to make concessions.
